answer:
1. Cut the four upper fingers of the latex glove so that the thumb remains intact. Cut a 30cm piece of silicone tube in the same way (see FASE 1);
2. Take the glove just cut and insert it into the larger 250ml beaker using a piece of paper tape to ensure a good seal. Then insert the silicone tube into the glove and secure it with a plastic clip (see FASE 2);
3. Insert the free end of the silicone tube into the U-shaped drying tube. In this case, too, secure everything with a piece of paper tape (see FASE 3);
4. Position the pliers and the plastic base so that you can support the smaller 100ml beaker in one of the two pliers, then place the U-shaped drying tube inside and close its free end with the rubber stopper (see FASE 4);
5. Move back to the larger 250ml beaker and cut the thumb from the tip. Use the scissors to cut the latex glove into a small piece of about 2cm. Insert the small piece of latex glove into the smaller 100ml beaker and secure it with a piece of paper tape (see FASE 5);
6. Fill the larger 250ml beaker with a water-alcohol mixture and place it on the tripod. Place the smaller 100ml beaker on the tripod and place the U-shaped drying tube inside. Close the free end of the U-shaped drying tube with the rubber stopper (see FASE 6);
7. Place the thermometer in the larger 250ml beaker and start heating the water-alcohol mixture. When the temperature reaches 65°C, the alcohol present in the mixture begins to evaporate and flows through the silicone tube to the U-shaped drying tube, where it condenses due to the surface cooled by the ice in the beaker (see FASE 7);
8. During the entire extraction of the alcohol, the temperature measured with the thermometer will remain constant, its increase will therefore indicate the end of the alcohol in the mixture (see FASE 8);
9. When the alcohol extraction is complete, turn off the Bunsen burner and remove the smaller 100ml beaker from the tripod. Remove the U-shaped drying tube from the smaller 100ml beaker and place it in a beaker containing water. Close the free end of the U-shaped drying tube with the rubber stop
